== 6. Measurement-error budget ==

Real-world HRV measurement accumulates error from four independent
sources. A defensible operator-state inference accounts for all four:

* '''Sampling-rate quantization''' — a PPG sampled at 100 Hz
  resolves R-R intervals to ±10 ms, contributing roughly
  3 ms of RMS error to [[RMSSD]]. Mk0.5 uses 250 Hz (±4 ms,
  ~1 ms RMSSD error). Below 50 Hz, RMSSD becomes uninterpretable.
* '''Peak-detection jitter''' — algorithmic peak location varies
  by ~5 ms on clean PPG, ~30 ms on motion-contaminated PPG. This
  is the dominant error source in field deployment.
* '''Ectopic-beat contamination''' — a single missed or extra
  beat injects a several-hundred-ms difference into the successive-
  difference series; one ectopic per 100 beats can double the
  reported RMSSD. Artefact correction is mandatory.
* '''Breathing-rate confound''' — RMSSD is a function of
  respiration rate. Comparing morning RMSSD across days requires
  controlling for breathing rate, ideally by paced breathing.

Mk0.5 implements a pre-registered artefact-correction pipeline
(threshold-based ectopic removal + cubic-spline interpolation +
breathing-rate covariate) before the L1 coherence metric is
computed.

