== 9. Falsification-criterion mapping ==

How HRV-and-ψ engages the [[Falsification_Criteria_for_Psionics|F1–F11]]
programme:

* '''F2 (population-level operator-state predictor)''' —
  HRV-state-conditioned ψ-task effect size is a direct test of F2.
* '''F3 (resonance enhancement)''' — the Mk2.0 closed-loop
  envelope scan at 6.5–9.5 Hz uses HRV as the
  state-of-engagement covariate.
* '''F4 (SAR-independence)''' — controlling for HRV state
  is required to separate ψ-effect from thermal-artefact.

HRV does not directly engage F1, F5–F11. It is the substrate
biomarker every other endpoint inherits from.

